This paper is about using deep learning for automated segmentation of head and neck anatomy from CT images. The paper specifically focuses on the use of a 3D U-net architecture with novel encoding schemes and loss functions to address challenges in segmenting small anatomies and dealing with inconsistent data annotations. Given this focus on deep learning and computer vision techniques for image segmentation, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
